    Scope and Contents
STEAMBOATS AND INLAND RIVERS 
Lyle, clerk and river agent, recalls the rivermen, boats, roustabouts, carpenters, wharfs, and wharf workers he encountered on rivers in Ohio and the Midwest. He also talks about boat building and the lumber industry in Cincinnati. 1 tape, 19 pp. 
Interview by John Knoepfle, 1957 
